paragraphs.title: Get Market Data
paragraphs.text:
import java.text.SimpleDateFormat
import java.sql.Date

case class MarketData(date :Date, open: Double, high: Double, low: Double, close: Double, vol: Int, product: String)

// load 3 files
val amtd = sc.textFile("/user/root/amtd.csv")
val oil = sc.textFile("/user/root/oil.csv")
val luv = sc.textFile("/user/root/luv.csv")

// map the data to schema
val amtdRDD = amtd.filter(f=> !f.contains("Close"))
  .map(_.split(","))
  .map(x=> MarketData(new Date (new SimpleDateFormat("dd-MMM-yy").parse(x(0)).getTime), 
       x(1).toDouble, x(2).toDouble, x(3).toDouble, x(4).toDouble, x(5).toInt, "amtd"  ))

val oilRDD = oil.filter(f=> !f.contains("Close"))
  .map(_.split(","))
  .map(x=> MarketData(new java.sql.Date (new SimpleDateFormat("dd-MMM-yy").parse(x(0)).getTime), 
       x(1).toDouble, x(2).toDouble, x(3).toDouble, x(4).toDouble, x(5).toInt, "oil" ))

val luvRDD = luv.filter(f=> !f.contains("Close"))
  .map(_.split(","))
  .map(x=> MarketData(new java.sql.Date (new SimpleDateFormat("dd-MMM-yy").parse(x(0)).getTime), 
       x(1).toDouble, x(2).toDouble, x(3).toDouble, x(4).toDouble, x(5).toInt, "luv" ))

// union the data
val marketData = amtdRDD ++ oilRDD ++ luvRDD


// register temp table
marketData.toDF.registerTempTable("marketData")

case class Text(comment: String)

val positive = "I really like that website.  It is modern and clean, the design is really cool.  I think it might be the one."
val neutral = "I'm not so sure about that website, it was just OK."
val negative = "I hate that website, it is dated looking and the features are really bad"
val comment1 = "I dislike the site, the features are stupid"

val df = Seq(Text(positive),Text(neutral),Text(negative), Text(comment1) ).toDF

df.registerTempTable("text")
